getCachedAttributeValue

public Object getCachedAttributeValue(Symbol attrName,
                                      Object defaultValue)
This method looks up a value of an attribute in the Items local Cache and does not cause an RPC call to G2 for the item. When Items are sent from G2 to Java BY-COPY-AND-HANDLE, they may be created with pre initialized attribute values sent from G2. This method can be used to retrieve these values without causing an RPC call to G2.

isItemLocal

public boolean isItemLocal()
Is this object operating remotely ? An G2 Item sent from G2 can be sent as; 1. "BY HANDLE" in which case this Item represents a remote G2 object. 2. "BY COPY" the object is locally held and has no relation to an exisiting G2 Object.

isInstanceOfG2Class

public boolean isInstanceOfG2Class(Symbol g2ClassName_)
The G2 named equivalent of instanceof. Use instead of getting the class from G2 in order to call instanceOf(). This method doesn't require that the class named by g2ClassName_ be loaded on the client.
Returns:
true if " is a " would return true for this item in G2, false otherwise

getDefinition

public G2Definition getDefinition()
                           throws G2AccessException
Returns a G2Definition object corresponding to the class of this Item. If this is an instance of a user-defined class then the G2Definition will be a Definition (an abstract class). It will be one of : ClassDefinition, ObjectDefinition, MessageDefinition, or ConnectionDefinition.
Returns:
A G2Defintiion for the class of this Item
Throws:
G2AccessException - if there are any communication problems

isValid

public boolean isValid()
Return the validity status of an item. An item becomes invalid if there has been a change in or deletion of the item on the G2 side.

setAttributeWritesAreCached

public void setAttributeWritesAreCached(boolean status)
If called with true any attributes set on a "by-handle" item will not be written to the G2 item, but cached until flushAttributeWriteCache is called.
Parameters:
status - set true to enable the AttributeWritesCache.

isAttributeWritesCached

public boolean isAttributeWritesCached()
Return the status of the AttributeWriteCache.
Returns:
false == The AttributeWriteCache is disabled, any attribute sets will be passed to the G2 item (default). true == The AttributeWriteCache is enabled, any attribute sets will be not be passed to G2, until flushAttributeWriteCache is called.

flushAttributeWriteCache

public void flushAttributeWriteCache()
                              throws G2AccessException
Send any attribute updates currently "waiting" to be written back to the item in G2 from the AttributeWriteCache. The attribute changes are sent using one network call.
